droop /druːp/

(drooping,drooped,droops) 

1. V-I If something droops , it hangs or leans downward with no strength or firmness. 下垂 

例： Crook's eyelids drooped and he yawned. 克鲁克的眼睑垂了下来，打起了呵欠。 

2. N-SING Droop is also a noun. 下垂 

例： ...the droop of his shoulders. …他肩膀的耷拉像。

